06:17.663 --> 06:19.196
It's not a scam, Frank.

06:19.231 --> 06:21.031
Neil and I are in love.

06:21.067 --> 06:22.966
And he's brain-injured, not deaf.

06:23.002 --> 06:24.535
Aren't they cute?

06:24.570 --> 06:26.637
[Monica] Neil reminds
me of that pet hamster

06:26.672 --> 06:28.105
- Debbie had as a kid.
- [Frank chuckles]

06:28.140 --> 06:29.173
The one you killed in the bathtub.

06:29.208 --> 06:30.374
You remember that, Frank?

06:30.409 --> 06:31.608
Yeah... that... it was a total accident.

06:31.644 --> 06:33.777
I was told hamsters could swim.

06:33.813 --> 06:36.146
- Mm.
- Debbie's in love.

06:36.182 --> 06:38.515
Love is not supposed to be cute.

06:38.551 --> 06:40.484
Love is raw

06:40.519 --> 06:42.720
and destructive.

06:42.755 --> 06:45.389
Love is you almost
stabbing me in the heart

06:45.424 --> 06:47.391
with an ice-pick when we
were having an argument.

06:47.426 --> 06:49.660
That's the kind of
passion you can't fake.

06:49.695 --> 06:52.029
Well, Neil and I don't need passion.

06:52.064 --> 06:53.964
Come on, Franny,

06:53.999 --> 06:56.367
let's go give Daddy a bath
before Mommy has to go to work.

06:56.402 --> 06:58.802
Bye, Franny.

06:58.838 --> 07:00.070
Bye, Deb.

07:03.509 --> 07:06.043
Our thrills don't have to end.

07:06.078 --> 07:08.245
You goddamn right they don't.

07:08.280 --> 07:10.547
You and me, we are immortal.

07:10.583 --> 07:11.749
[giggles]

07:11.784 --> 07:15.185
So I want to show you my plan.

07:15.221 --> 07:17.054
I want to see your plan.

07:17.089 --> 07:19.289
Hey.

07:22.528 --> 07:23.894
Aww, honey.

07:23.929 --> 07:25.362
Whoa.

07:25.398 --> 07:27.164
[Monica] You look like shit.

07:27.199 --> 07:29.533
Looking like a chip off
the old block there, son.

07:29.568 --> 07:31.001
Did you go on a bender alone?

07:31.036 --> 07:32.870
Fuck off, huh?

07:32.905 --> 07:34.171
Booze bums you out.

07:34.206 --> 07:35.506
Change chemicals.

07:35.549 --> 07:37.051
[chuckling]

07:37.076 --> 07:39.543
All right, well, next time
we'll all get shitfaced together.

07:39.545 --> 07:41.412
I'd rather drink my own piss.

07:41.447 --> 07:43.614
Try a speedball after a bender.

07:43.649 --> 07:46.450
Next day, you'll be moving like a pro.

07:46.485 --> 07:47.751
[chuckles]

07:47.787 --> 07:50.256
Come on, Frankie, follow me.

07:50.589 --> 07:52.423
Come on.

07:52.458 --> 07:53.891
A stash?

07:53.926 --> 07:55.159
Wrong.

07:57.596 --> 07:58.729
Ta-da.

07:58.731 --> 08:00.597
I was kind of hoping for cocaine.

08:00.633 --> 08:03.100
Oh, we're gonna get all the
cocaine we want with these.

08:03.135 --> 08:04.201
We're gonna sell 'em?

08:04.236 --> 08:05.302
No, we're gonna use 'em.

08:05.337 --> 08:07.738
Frank, I want to write a will...

08:07.773 --> 08:10.140
I don't have anything
solid to leave the kids.

08:10.176 --> 08:12.142
Those kids don't need an inheritance.

08:12.178 --> 08:13.577
It'll ruin 'em.

08:13.612 --> 08:16.313
Look, I lifted this
from my old dealer, Eric.

08:16.348 --> 08:19.116
He had a plan to rub
a police evidence room

08:19.151 --> 08:21.552
and get off with the drugs and the cash.

08:21.587 --> 08:23.058
How much cash?

08:23.083 --> 08:26.056
Eh, those aces hold
like 75 to 100 grand.

08:26.091 --> 08:28.926
If we get off with half,
we're golden, Frankie.

08:28.961 --> 08:32.261
Wouldn't it be great to
be outlaws together again?

08:32.298 --> 08:34.664
We could just get wasted together again.

08:34.700 --> 08:37.768
No, remember all the thrills
we had when we were kids?

08:37.803 --> 08:40.504
When I used to lure guys into the hotel

08:40.539 --> 08:42.806
and lock the bathroom
door so we could run off

08:42.842 --> 08:44.107
with their wallets and drugs?

08:44.143 --> 08:45.442
Sweet bird of youth.

08:45.478 --> 08:46.777
Yes.

08:46.812 --> 08:48.946
Look, I want to leave each kid

08:48.981 --> 08:52.683
five grand so they can
get a good start in life.

08:52.718 --> 08:55.752
Will you help me make amends, Frankie?

08:55.788 --> 08:57.120
- Want some?
- Yeah.

08:57.156 --> 08:59.957
Ohh, thank you.

08:59.992 --> 09:03.358
[cell phone buzzes]

09:04.140 --> 09:05.973
That's the fifth time
she's called this morning.

09:06.017 --> 09:07.249
Let her bake.

09:07.285 --> 09:09.385
I'm pissed.

09:09.420 --> 09:11.153
And I still really don't
understand what happened.

09:11.189 --> 09:13.889
Deed, business license, liquor license,

09:13.925 --> 09:16.726
bill of sale, all with
our signatures on it.

09:16.862 --> 09:18.139
That looks just like my handwriting.

09:18.164 --> 09:19.732
Because it is. Mine too.

09:19.757 --> 09:22.264
How does Svetlana own
our bar and our girls?

09:22.300 --> 09:23.933
Not our girls, just our bar.

09:23.968 --> 09:26.168
