Thanks? How are things at home?

28:36.980 --> 28:39.614
Oh, V might be literally burning
the house down as we speak.

28:39.649 --> 28:41.215
What?

28:41.251 --> 28:43.117
Svetlana made us sign
some phony adoption papers

28:43.153 --> 28:44.686
and now she owns The Alibi.

28:44.721 --> 28:45.787
She took your bar?

28:45.822 --> 28:47.188
[sighs] V's on a rampage.

28:47.223 --> 28:48.766
She wants to burn all of her clothes.

28:48.791 --> 28:50.358
And frankly, I'm afraid
of my own wife right now.

28:50.393 --> 28:51.938
Svetlana stole your bar?

28:51.962 --> 28:54.072
She's like a sexy Russian ninja.

28:54.097 --> 28:55.963
It blows 'cause we're
either out of a job

28:55.999 --> 28:57.832
or we have to work for her.

28:57.867 --> 29:00.201
Or we could sue her but
we can't afford a lawyer.

29:00.236 --> 29:02.203
And that OJ lawyer guy's already dead

29:02.238 --> 29:04.115
That is so fucked.

29:04.941 --> 29:06.541
You should call my divorce attorney,

29:06.576 --> 29:08.009
the guy that got me out
of the marriage with Gus.

29:08.044 --> 29:10.478
- He's a shark.
- Oh, also,

29:10.513 --> 29:12.847
I know you and V still
kind of hate each other,

29:12.882 --> 29:14.315
but she seriously misses you.

29:14.350 --> 29:15.850
Do you think you can talk to her

29:15.885 --> 29:17.585
before she kills Svetlana?

29:17.620 --> 29:19.209
Or me?

29:19.373 --> 29:22.190
Uhh... I gotta handle something.

29:22.225 --> 29:24.058
Can you, uh, can you talk more later?

29:24.094 --> 29:26.060
Yeah-yeah, sure, can you just
text me that lawyer's info?

29:26.096 --> 29:28.329
- Yeah.
- Thanks.

29:28.364 --> 29:30.998
[Chad] Well, the outside
perimeter is 30x24.

29:31.034 --> 29:32.867
So I'll have them send an
estimate as soon as they're done.

29:32.902 --> 29:34.368
Hey. What's going on?

29:34.404 --> 29:36.938
Margo thinks you're fucking with
her, trying to raise the bid.

29:36.973 --> 29:38.773
I'm not, I just don't want to sell.

29:38.808 --> 29:40.875
You got a lot of folks
throwing 90 grand at you?

29:40.910 --> 29:42.276
It's not about the money.

29:42.312 --> 29:44.445
I-I mean, I-I fixed
this place up myself.

29:44.488 --> 29:47.181
I could have jumped ship right
after I bought it and I didn't.

29:47.217 --> 29:48.716
It's important to me.

29:48.752 --> 29:51.052
And to all the people in this
neighborhood who come here.

29:51.087 --> 29:52.909
How much did you spend on repairs?

29:53.223 --> 29:54.522
About 8,000.

29:54.549 --> 29:55.849
So counter Margo at a hundred grand

29:55.892 --> 29:57.176
and get ten Gs in profits.

29:57.201 --> 29:58.426
But I wouldn't push
it further than that.

29:58.461 --> 30:00.261
[scoffs] A hundred grand?

30:00.296 --> 30:02.063
Yeah, she'll probably go that high.

30:02.098 --> 30:04.799
But she's got a lot of
irons in the fire, so...

30:04.834 --> 30:06.887
she might walk if you don't move fast.

30:23.686 --> 30:26.257
[indistinct radio chatter]

30:28.124 --> 30:29.891
Ma'am?

30:29.926 --> 30:31.926
- Everything okay here?
- Peachy.

30:31.961 --> 30:34.095
Happen to notice the
fire in your front yard?

30:34.130 --> 30:36.597
[fire crackling]

30:36.633 --> 30:37.965
Husband piss you off?

30:38.001 --> 30:39.667
Wife.

30:39.702 --> 30:41.469
Wife?

30:41.504 --> 30:43.013
Clothes are good and singed.

30:43.038 --> 30:45.339
- Just put it out, okay?
- Yep.

30:45.375 --> 30:47.975
And if you see any suspicious
activity in the neighborhood,

30:48.011 --> 30:49.037
be sure to report it.

30:49.062 --> 30:52.225
We have reason to believe there's a
couple of escaped convicts in the area.

30:55.285 --> 30:56.398
Let's go.

31:00.984 --> 31:03.601
I was a shit mom, Frankie...

31:03.626 --> 31:06.194
and a shit wife, and I know that.

31:06.229 --> 31:07.929
You're my wild card.

31:07.964 --> 31:10.374
No game's worth playing without one.

31:11.234 --> 31:13.467
You always make room
for me to crawl back in,

31:13.503 --> 31:15.102
but not the kids.

31:15.138 --> 31:17.171
Because they're fucking ingrates.

31:17.207 --> 31:18.339
You're a great mom.

31:18.374 --> 31:19.507
No.

31:19.542 --> 31:21.042
I'm crazy.

31:21.077 --> 31:23.344
I know that and I can't fix it.

31:23.379 --> 31:25.780
But leaving them the money is something.

31:25.815 --> 31:27.481
We gotta make another plan.

31:27.517 --> 31:29.550
[brakes hiss]

31:29.586 --> 31:31.352
Sweet destiny,

31:31.387 --> 31:33.054
what have we here?

31:33.089 --> 31:34.989
[Frank] A casino bus.

31:35.024 --> 31:36.157
[laugh]

31:37.193 --> 31:40.528
I think I know our next target.

31:40.563 --> 31:43.030
- Yes! Yes!
- [chuckling]

31:43.066 --> 31:45.833
Hey? Burgers.

31:45.869 --> 31:47.401
From that new Shake Shack.

31:47.437 --> 31:50.004
You, uh... got time for a bite?

31:50.039 --> 31:52.073
Ah, I'm the middle of work shit.

31:52.098 --> 31:55.016
I have to find placement for two
of my teens before the morning.

31:55.051 --> 31:56.310
Homeless shelter's overbooked.

31:56.346 --> 31:57.645
Oh, sounds pretty hectic.

31:57.680 --> 31:59.247
Yeah, like epic level.

31:59.273 --> 32:01.840
Gia got kicked out for
pulling a knife on some chick

32:01.885 --> 32:04.151
that she swears was stealing
her bras from the wash.

32:04.187 --> 32:05.285
It's...

32:05.310 --> 32:07.154
I'm letting her crash at my
place for a couple of nights

32:07.190 --> 32:08.556
until we get her situated.

32:08.591 --> 32:09.857
Fucking crazy day.

32:09.893 --> 32:11.826
I bet mine was crazier.

32:11.861 --> 32:12.894
[cell phone rings]

32:12.929 --> 32:14.495
Oh, hold on one second.

32:14.530 --> 32:16.613
Hey, Dina, what's up?

32:16.766 --> 32:18.766
No-no-no-no, uh, tell
'em to keep a slot open.

32:18.791 --> 32:20.167
I-I'll bring her over right now.

32:20.203 --> 32:21.836
Okay. Yeah, bye.

32:21.871 --> 32:23.237
You gotta bounce?

32:23.273 --> 32:26.106
Yeah, there's an opening at
Project Fierce for one of my kids.

32:26.131 --> 32:27.478
It's a buzzer beater.

32:27.520 --> 32:30.244
Uh, do you mind if I
take this to go, or...?

32:30.280 --> 32:31.679
Yeah-yeah-yeah, sure.

32:31.714 --> 32:32.947
But, hey, I'm gonna
call you later because

32:32.982 --> 32:34.723
I want to hear about your crazy day.

32:40.490 --> 32:43.457
[upbeat hip-hop music playing]

32:43.493 --> 32:48.496
♪

32:51.134 --> 32:53.367
Denise Wright?

32:53.403 --> 32:54.735
Washer number seven.

32:59.342 --> 33:00.608
Couple of old guys over there

33:00.643 --> 33:01.909
complaining about the loud music.

33:01.945 --> 33:03.144
Might need to start a Senior Wash.

33:03.212 --> 33:04.545
We've only made a profit so far

33:04.580 --> 33:06.147
of-of 20 bucks at the Mat tonight.

33:06.182 --> 33:07.449
How is that possible?

33:07.474 --> 33:09.464
Couple more weeks like
this and you're cash.

33:09.489 --> 33:11.237
You're stressed cause
of that Margo lady?

33:11.262 --> 33:12.828
Well, I'm thinking about her offer.

33:12.855 --> 33:14.316
What about Etta?

33:14.604 --> 33:16.121
Well, I didn't say I was taking it,

33:16.146 --> 33:18.280
but I'm-I'm trying to think
of good reasons not to.

33:18.305 --> 33:20.672
'Cause we're South Siders
and we don't sell out.

33:20.697 --> 33:22.973
'Cause your sister's
making really good tips.

33:26.669 --> 33:29.737
[indistinct TV chatter]

33:29.772 --> 33:31.606
[man] Forty bucks.

33:41.317 --> 33:42.516
- [slurred murmuring]
- Go right up.

33:42.552 --> 33:45.953
[laugh] You... okay.

33:45.989 --> 33:47.688
- I-I....
- What?

33:47.724 --> 33:49.156
[laughs]

33:49.192 --> 33:50.925
- Hold me up, hold me up.
- Okay.

33:50.960 --> 33:52.493
- [laughing] I... no, wait.
- Hold on, what are you doing?

33:52.528 --> 33:54.996
- I can't...
- Oh, you're...

33:55.031 --> 33:56.998
No, I got it. I got it.

33:57.033 --> 33:58.586
Oh, no, this is the first one.

33:58.611 --> 34:00.892
Okay, and then...

34:01.704 --> 34:03.604
[laughing]

34:03.639 --> 34:05.306
Shit.

34:05.341 --> 34:07.329
- We're locked out.
- The f...

34:07.354 --> 34:09.400
Shh.

34:10.313 --> 34:12.013
The fuck?

34:12.047 --> 34:13.380
We can't...

34:13.416 --> 34:15.216
where we gonna sleep?

34:15.251 --> 34:16.717
There's gotta be another way in.

34:16.745 --> 34:18.311
<i>♪ bluesy rock music ♪</i>

34:18.353 --> 34:20.844
Shh! Yeah.

34:20.870 --> 34:21.989
All right.

34:22.025 --> 34:23.623
<i>♪</i>

34:23.659 --> 34:24.775
Ahh.

34:24.985 --> 34:26.083
Careful.

34:26.134 --> 34:27.495
I know.

34:27.530 --> 34:29.496
- Yes!
- Yeah!

34:29.532 --> 34:31.232
Well done.

34:31.266 --> 34:34.563
<i>♪</i>

34:34.904 --> 34:36.337
Wait. Oh!

34:36.371 --> 34:37.737
- [thud]
- Ow!

34:37.763 --> 34:39.290
<i>♪</i>

34:39.409 --> 34:41.351
- Here.
- Yes. Okay.

34:41.376 --> 34:44.344
<i>♪</i>

34:44.347 --> 34:46.547
[grunts]

34:46.581 --> 34:49.250
[Monica] Oh. Yes.

34:49.284 --> 34:50.583
Hey, what do you think
you're doing, Frank?

34:50.620 --> 34:51.685
- I...
- No, wait!

34:51.721 --> 34:52.754
I told you there's a curfew.

34:52.779 --> 34:54.579
- Yeah, but wait...
- We-we lost track of time.

34:54.603 --> 34:56.857
You're already on thin ice
bringing Frank around here.

34:56.893 --> 34:58.592
- Oh, my God.
- You can't separate

34:58.628 --> 35:01.662
Frank and Monica. We're Lucy and Desi,

35:01.697 --> 35:05.305
Barack and Michelle, Sonny and Cher.

35:05.330 --> 35:08.064
I only know who, like,
two of those people are.

35:17.947 --> 35:19.880
What time is it?

35:19.916 --> 35:23.084
It's, uh, around midnight.

35:23.119 --> 35:25.786
[yawns]

35:25.822 --> 35:27.788
[chuckles] You doing homework?

35:27.824 --> 35:29.457
Yeah.

35:29.492 --> 35:31.792
I was trying to calculate
how long it would take me

35:31.828 --> 35:35.062
to make a profit of $10,000 at the Mat.

35:36.632 --> 35:38.732
After I got past three years,

35:38.768 --> 35:40.367
I think brain shut off.

35:40.403 --> 35:42.203
That long?

35:42.238 --> 35:44.038
Yeah.

35:44.073 --> 35:46.774
[sighs]

35:46.809 --> 35:48.609
[cell phone buzzes]

35:52.148 --> 35:53.747
What are you doing up?

35:53.783 --> 35:55.316
I couldn't sleep.

35:57.019 --> 35:58.452
You ever, uh,

35:58.488 --> 35:59.753
think about what would have happened

35:59.789 --> 36:02.289
if you ran off with Jimmy-Steve?

36:06.496 --> 36:07.728
[scoff]

36:07.763 --> 36:10.030
Lying sociopath Jimmy-Steve?

36:11.100 --> 36:13.700
My life would be a...

36:14.637 --> 36:18.349
non-stop psycho thriller.

36:18.975 --> 36:21.677
And I definitely dodged
a bullet with that one.

36:22.311 --> 36:25.479
What if nothing ever gives
you that same thrill again?

36:25.515 --> 36:28.849
Will you still feel
like you dodged a bullet?

36:31.287 --> 36:32.620
I don't know.

36:35.191 --> 36:37.024
Probably.

36:37.059 --> 36:39.527
Where's this coming from?

36:39.562 --> 36:42.863
Things have been weird between
me and Trev since Mickey got out.

36:42.899 --> 36:45.299
You mean since Mickey
busted out of prison

36:45.324 --> 36:49.503
and has got half the
Chicago Police Department

36:49.539 --> 36:51.605
circling the South Side looking for him?

36:51.641 --> 36:54.335
[scoffs] Can't get him out of my head.

36:55.878 --> 36:57.878
I'm just trying to stop myself

36:57.914 --> 36:59.813
from doing something I shouldn't.

36:59.849 --> 37:01.849
You turned your life around.

37:05.021 --> 37:08.322
Mickey would set a match to it.

37:08.357 --> 37:11.358
You've done really great without him.

37:13.429 --> 37:15.930
And I'm really fucking proud of you.

37:22.939 --> 37:24.838
I'm gonna see if I can get

37:24.874 --> 37:26.807
a few hours in an actual bed.

37:26.842 --> 37:28.741
Yeah.

37:29.712 --> 37:31.476
- Night.
- Good night.

37:35.907 --> 37:38.908
[stairs creaking]

37:40.523 --> 37:42.256
[cell phone buzzes]

38:04.247 --> 38:05.646
Knew you'd come.

38:08.251 --> 38:09.862
Knew you'd come.

38:09.887 --> 38:11.854
Come here.

38:20.630 --> 38:22.863
[scoffs] The fuck?

38:22.898 --> 38:24.531
What, you think my life hasn't moved on

38:24.567 --> 38:26.300
since you were locked up, Mickey?

38:26.335 --> 38:27.968
No, I just thought that
you'd be down for me

38:28.004 --> 38:29.603
since the whole reason I
did time was going after

38:29.639 --> 38:31.071
the bitch who tried to ruin you.

38:31.107 --> 38:32.906
I'm not pissing away my life...

38:32.942 --> 38:34.742
Stop.

38:39.074 --> 38:40.281
Fuck!

38:42.184 --> 38:44.418
I have my shit together, Mick!

38:44.453 --> 38:47.921
And I-I have a-a fucking boyfriend!

38:47.957 --> 38:49.490
Boyfriend?

38:51.827 --> 38:53.460
Okay.

38:56.432 --> 38:59.400
What you doing here then?

38:59.435 --> 39:00.834
Hmm?

39:07.176 --> 39:09.310
Tell me good-bye.

39:12.515 --> 39:13.681
What?

39:23.859 --> 39:25.459
Fuck.

39:33.636 --> 39:35.969
[pained groan]

39:36.005 --> 39:38.339
[heavy breathing]

39:38.374 --> 39:41.542
[intense white noise]

39:41.577 --> 39:44.578
[high-pitched ringing]

39:47.383 --> 39:49.183
Oh, no.

39:53.923 --> 39:56.633
Oh... hey.

39:58.427 --> 40:00.060
[murmuring]

40:02.762 --> 40:04.562
- [thud]
- Fuck.

40:04.587 --> 40:07.221
Ah, fuck.

40:07.246 --> 40:10.247
[panting]

40:11.374 --> 40:12.539
Lip?

40:12.575 --> 40:14.308
Hey. [murmurs]

40:14.343 --> 40:16.176
[Lip] Helene.

40:16.212 --> 40:18.379
You broke into my home?

40:18.414 --> 40:20.080
What?

40:20.116 --> 40:21.382
Are you insane?

40:21.448 --> 40:22.881
[panting]

40:24.778 --> 40:27.250
You can't be here.

40:31.427 --> 40:33.060
Jesus, Lip.

40:33.095 --> 40:36.096
[breathy mumbling]

40:41.470 --> 40:43.904
You've got to move on.

40:45.775 --> 40:47.441
Please.

40:49.044 --> 40:51.845
Get some help.

40:51.881 --> 40:54.848
<i>♪ somber rock music ♪</i>

40:54.884 --> 40:59.887
<i>♪</i>

41:02.458 --> 41:04.057
[door handle clicks]

41:04.093 --> 41:09.096
<i>♪</i>

41:39.094 --> 41:42.312
<i>♪</i>

42:12.528 --> 42:14.628
[phone line trilling]

42:14.663 --> 42:15.729
[groans]

42:17.633 --> 42:19.600
[Trevor] <i> What's up? It's
Trevor. Leave me a message.</i>

42:19.635 --> 42:20.922
<i>- Make it good.</i>
- [beep]

42:20.947 --> 42:23.081
Hey, uh,

42:23.205 --> 42:24.771
sorry I missed you.

42:24.807 --> 42:27.133
Text me if you want to hook up later.

42:28.711 --> 42:29.877
[whispers] I miss you.

42:29.912 --> 42:31.178
Bye.

42:38.351 --> 42:39.527
Hey.

42:39.555 --> 42:41.288
- [gasps]
- Hey.

42:41.323 --> 42:42.456
[groans]

42:42.491 --> 42:43.891
- I gotta go.
- The fuck?

42:43.926 --> 42:46.359
- [groans]
- Back to work and shit.

42:47.329 --> 42:49.229
[exhales]

42:51.789 --> 42:53.422
I'm gonna see you again?

43:07.249 --> 43:08.448
Ahh.

43:12.337 --> 43:13.754
[Tin Man] And him a brain.

43:13.789 --> 43:16.657
[Dorothy] <i> Why, you're nothing</i>
<i>but a great big coward.</i>

43:16.692 --> 43:18.492
- Hey, buddy.
- Huh?

43:18.527 --> 43:21.028
Debs leave you here while
she went to work all day?

43:21.063 --> 43:22.996
Why do you smell like death and beer?

43:23.032 --> 43:24.398
[Cowardly Lion] <i> Scare myself.</i>

43:24.433 --> 43:27.167
It's called "living," son.

43:27.202 --> 43:30.704
Maybe Neil would like
to live a little too?

43:30.739 --> 43:32.506
Want to?

43:32.541 --> 43:33.840
Could be some weed

43:33.876 --> 43:36.376
and ice cream in it for ya.

43:36.412 --> 43:39.379
Debbie doesn't let me have
ice cream because of lactose.

43:39.407 --> 43:42.374
What kind of a woman
denies her man lactose?

43:42.418 --> 43:44.723
[inhales sharply] You just
don't need to tell her.

43:44.748 --> 43:46.161
[Dorothy] <i> Why don't
you come along with us?</i>

43:46.186 --> 43:47.462
Cool.

43:47.489 --> 43:48.956
[Dorothy] <i> We're on our way
to see The Wizard now.</i>

43:48.991 --> 43:50.791
A hundred grand's a lot
of money for that dump.

43:50.826 --> 43:54.127
Twenty-five percent profit in 60 days.

43:54.163 --> 43:57.097
Are you really gonna
walk away from that?

43:57.132 --> 43:59.132
What's the obstacle here, Gallagher?

43:59.168 --> 44:00.968
I promised Etta Tesdale a place to live

44:01.003 --> 44:02.069
if she sold me her lease.

44:02.104 --> 44:03.109
Who?

44:03.134 --> 44:05.314
The old lady that I
bought the laundromat from.

44:05.674 --> 44:07.074
She's got her cats.

44:07.109 --> 44:09.476
She sits in her chair every day.

44:09.511 --> 44:11.144
Where's she gonna go?

44:11.172 --> 44:13.439
Well, you can take
her cats and her chair

44:13.482 --> 44:16.617
and put her in assisted living.

44:16.652 --> 44:19.586
She probably won't even
know the difference.

44:19.622 --> 44:21.955
They get to play lots
of bingo. They love that.

44:21.991 --> 44:24.257
I'm starting to turn a profit.

44:24.293 --> 44:26.627
My family works there.

44:26.662 --> 44:28.829
People in the neighborhood depend on it.

44:28.864 --> 44:31.531
Why should I sell if I'm doing well?

44:32.468 --> 44:34.675
You're smarter than you look.

44:34.870 --> 44:37.589
All right, name your
price. Hundred and twenty?

44:38.525 --> 44:39.858
[inhales deeply]

44:39.883 --> 44:43.610
I-I just don't think that my
conscience will allow me to sell.

44:43.646 --> 44:46.370
You've been doing your research, huh?

44:47.116 --> 44:50.042
I'm redeveloping the whole block.

44:50.653 --> 44:53.253
So I will give you 160,000,

44:53.288 --> 44:55.288
which is double what
you paid for that lease.

44:55.324 --> 44:59.839
It is that or I will go
redevelop another shitty block.

44:59.995 --> 45:03.261
And there are plenty of
those left around here.

45:05.334 --> 45:08.535
So this offer expires
at the end of the day.

45:14.743 --> 45:17.034
Okay. [sniffs]

45:17.379 --> 45:19.613
As soon as he starts his
engine, we make our move.

45:19.648 --> 45:22.949
Son, dive down low, at an angle,

45:22.985 --> 45:25.152
so you... you don't get run over, okay?

45:25.187 --> 45:26.687
If you scrape your face or bleed,

45:26.722 --> 45:28.822
- that would be great.
- [bus engine turns over]

45:28.857 --> 45:30.524
Okay.

45:30.559 --> 45:31.860
- Go.
- Yes.

45:34.954 --> 45:36.086
[thuds]

45:36.119 --> 45:37.528
[brakes hiss]

45:37.553 --> 45:39.066
- Ah!
- Oh, my God.

45:39.101 --> 45:41.268
- Ah!
